ent) CAN create havoc!&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&=\r\ngt;One may wonder how Kundalini may spontaneously rise in a layman with no =\r\nsadhana, while many serious sadhakas may not experience it.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt=\r\n;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Firstly, Kundalini rise is NOT an achievement. It i=\r\ns just A SMALL&lt;BR&gt;&gt; STEP in overcoming one&#39;s current limited identity.&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Let me give an analogy. One wanting t=\r\no move from one&#39;s small dilapidated house (this&lt;BR&gt;&gt; body-mind complex)\n=\r\n to a huge palace (realized Self) may first construct the palace over time =\r\nand move into it when it is COMPLETE. Alternately, if one occasionally goes=\r\n and stays in the palace still under construction (analogy for out of body =\r\nexperiences due to Kundalini rise), is it an achievement? In fact, it comes=\r\n with risks. The former approach is safer and one loses nothing in it. Simi=\r\nlarly, one can progress towards complete Self-realization without any out o=\r\nf body experiences. These are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words=\r\n to Lord Rama.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Secondly, one does no=\r\nt get something without wanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it=\r\n. One may have deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may h=\r\nave put enough effort. As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may =\r\nbe unprepared (and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this =\r\nlife.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try\n not to=\r\n fancy too many specific&lt;BR&gt;&gt; desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in g=\r\nranting your desires (because of constraints on what Nature can give you ri=\r\nght now, arising from YOUR&lt;BR&gt;&gt; OWN previous actions). So Nature sometim=\r\nes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want somethi=\r\nng else. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be=\r\n born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that weal=\r\nth and pray whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be very =\r\nhealthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In another &lt;BR&gt;&gt; case, one=\r\n may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn &lt;BR&gt;&gt; as a=\r\n tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that &lt;BR&gt;&gt=\r\n; experience. Basically, people keep going in circles through various lives=\r\n, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if one deeply\n desires an ou=\r\nt of body experience given by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas =\r\nconstrain one from having it in THIS life, one may be born in next life wit=\r\nh this specific desire destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik forc=\r\ne behind it).&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; *=\r\n&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily s=\r\ncary or painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachmen=\r\nt.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a =\r\nmouse trap. I went to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake=\r\n violently. I went to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared t=\r\nhat I would kill it!&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like tha=\r\nt chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex and scare=\r\nd of being rescued from a certain slow death!&lt;BR&gt;&gt;\n &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind comple=\r\nx) are incorrect and if we a